{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Unconditional revert in redeem policy freezes all redemptions, exits, and cToken transfers","locations":["onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:333","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:192","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:677","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/CToken.sol:405","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/CToken.sol:422"],"claim":"`redeemAllowedInternal()` unconditionally executes `revert(\"redeemer is paused\")` before any market-listing, membership, or liquidity checks. Every redemption path that consults the comptroller therefore aborts, and `transferAllowed()` reuses the same bricked hook.","impact":"Suppliers cannot redeem underlying, cannot exit markets, and cannot transfer cTokens. This creates a protocol-wide withdrawal and mobility freeze that can lock collateral until the comptroller implementation is replaced.","paths":["`redeem()`/`redeemUnderlying()` -> `redeemFresh()` -> `comptroller.redeemAllowed()` -> `redeemAllowedInternal()` -> unconditional revert","`exitMarket()` -> `redeemAllowedInternal()` -> unconditional revert","`transfer()`/`transferFrom()` on cTokens -> `comptroller.transferAllowed()` -> `redeemAllowedInternal()` -> unconditional revert"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Unconditional revert in repay policy disables repayments and liquidation repayments","locations":["onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:486","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/CToken.sol:591","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/CToken.sol:719","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:530"],"claim":"`repayBorrowAllowed()` unconditionally executes `revert(\"repay is paused\")`. Because `repayBorrowFresh()` always calls this hook first, both direct repayments and liquidation repayments revert before any debt reduction occurs.","impact":"Borrowers can open debt positions but cannot repay them, and liquidators cannot close unhealthy debt. Interest can continue accruing while bad debt becomes uncollectable, creating a credible path to protocol insolvency.","paths":["`repayBorrow()`/`repayBorrowBehalf()` -> `repayBorrowFresh()` -> `comptroller.repayBorrowAllowed()` -> unconditional revert","`liquidateBorrow()` -> `liquidateBorrowFresh()` -> `repayBorrowFresh()` -> `comptroller.repayBorrowAllowed()` -> unconditional revert"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"`accountAssets` is no longer capped, enabling gas-based DoS of liquidity and liquidation checks","locations":["onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/ComptrollerStorage.sol:47","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/ComptrollerStorage.sol:50","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:123","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:142","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:545","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:867"],"claim":"Storage still documents `accountAssets` as capped by `maxAssets`, but `enterMarkets()`/`addToMarketInternal()` never enforce any such limit. Liquidity and liquidation checks then iterate over the full `accountAssets` array and perform per-market snapshot and oracle work for every entered market.","impact":"If enough markets are listed, an attacker can join many markets with dust balances and make `borrowAllowed`, liquidity checks, and especially liquidations increasingly expensive. Once the account's asset set is large enough, essential risk checks can become impractical to execute within gas limits, allowing unhealthy positions to evade timely liquidation.","paths":["`enterMarkets()` across many listed markets -> unbounded growth of `accountAssets[attacker]`","`borrowAllowed()`/liquidity checks -> `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityInternal()` loops over all entered assets","`liquidateBorrowAllowed()` -> `getAccountLiquidityInternal()` -> `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityInternal()` loops over all entered assets"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Collateral-cap registration runs before membership checks, so repeated market entry can corrupt external collateral bookkeeping","locations":["onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:150","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:152","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/Comptroller.sol:155","onchain_auto/0x7aa375f1fe5e04e18a6b02b4294cfd57ca9f53ba/contracts/CTokenInterfaces.sol:432"],"claim":"For `COLLATERALCAP` markets, `addToMarketInternal()` invokes the external `registerCollateral()` hook before checking whether the borrower is already a member, and it ignores the hook's `uint256` return value. Repeated `enterMarkets()` calls on the same market therefore rely on the cToken hook being perfectly idempotent and revert-on-failure.","impact":"If any listed collateral-cap implementation performs additive accounting or reports failures via return code instead of revert, a user can repeatedly enter the same market to over-register collateral or silently desynchronize collateral-cap bookkeeping. That can overstate borrow capacity, bypass collateral accounting limits, or leave collateral permanently mis-accounted.","paths":["`enterMarkets([same collateral-cap market])` called repeatedly -> `addToMarketInternal()` -> `registerCollateral()` before membership guard -> return value ignored"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Redundant and Potentially Confusing Revert in redeemVerify","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`redeemVerify`'s zero-token sanity check is a defensive invariant, not a realistic protocol-harming vulnerability; normal redeem flows should not reach it with inconsistent parameters, and any revert rolls back atomically."}]}
